The latest stats from NetMarketShare show that Windows 10 is still behind Windows 7 on desktop, but it is catching up. The January 2018 statistics also revealed that Android 7.0 and iOS 11.2 are the most popular mobile operating systems, with 22.65% and 19.26% market share respectively. Android 6.0 follows closely behind iOS 11.2, with a market share of 17.97%. The most popular operating systems on desktop and mobile for January 2018 are detailed below.  